{"content":"---\ntitle: \"&lt;assemblyBinding&gt; Element for &lt;configuration&gt; | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.prod: \".net-framework\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"dotnet-clr\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"http://schemas.microsoft.com/.NetConfiguration/v2.0#configuration/assemblyBinding\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"VB\"\n  - \"CSharp\"\n  - \"C++\"\n  - \"jsharp\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"assemblyBinding Element\"\n  - \"<assemblyBinding> Element\"\nms.assetid: 6cc55983-b894-449b-8e26-b258e53939cd\ncaps.latest.revision: 6\nauthor: \"mcleblanc\"\nms.author: \"markl\"\nmanager: \"markl\"\n---\n# &lt;assemblyBinding&gt; Element for &lt;configuration&gt;\nSpecifies assembly binding policy at the configuration level.  \n  \n \\<configuration> Element  \n\\<assemblyBinding> Element for \\<configuration>  \n  \n## Syntax  \n  \n```  \n<assemblyBinding    \n   xmlns=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:asm.v1\">  \n</assemblyBinding>  \n```  \n  \n## Attributes and Elements  \n The following sections describe attributes, child elements, and parent elements.  \n  \n### Attributes  \n  \n|Attribute|Description|  \n|---------------|-----------------|  \n|`xmlns`|Required attribute.<br /><br /> Specifies the XML namespace required for assembly binding. Use the string \"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:asm.v1\" as the value.|  \n  \n### Child Elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<linkedConfiguration> Element](../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/linkedconfiguration-element.md)|Specifies a configuration file to include.|  \n  \n### Parent Elements  \n  \n|Element|Description|  \n|-------------|-----------------|  \n|[\\<configuration> Element](../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/configuration-element.md)|The root element in every configuration file used by the common language runtime and .NET Framework applications.|  \n  \n## Remarks  \n The [\\<linkedConfiguration> Element](../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/linkedconfiguration-element.md) simplifies the management of component assemblies by allowing application configuration files to include assembly configuration files in well-known locations, rather than duplicating assembly configuration settings.  \n  \n> [!NOTE]\n>  The `<linkedConfiguration>` element is not supported for applications with Windows side-by-side manifests.  \n  \n## Example  \n The following code example shows how to include a configuration file on the local hard disk.  \n  \n```  \n<configuration>  \n   <assemblyBinding xmlns=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:asm.v1\">  \n      <linkedConfiguration href=\"file://c:\\Program Files\\Contoso\\sharedConfig.xml\"/>  \n   </assemblyBinding>  \n</configuration>  \n```  \n  \n## See Also  \n [Configuration File Schema](../../../../docs/framework/configure-apps/file-schema/index.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[12,86],"content":"&lt;assemblyBinding&gt; Element for &lt;configuration&gt; | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>assemblyBinding<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> Element for <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;lt;</ph>configuration<ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph> | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,74],"source":"&lt;assemblyBinding&gt; Element for &lt;configuration&gt; | Microsoft Docs"}]},{"pos":[628,685],"content":"&lt;assemblyBinding&gt; Element for &lt;configuration&gt;","linkify":"&lt;assemblyBinding&gt; Element for &lt;configuration&gt;","nodes":[{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>assemblyBinding<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> Element for <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;lt;</ph>configuration<ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph>","pos":[0,57],"source":"&lt;assemblyBinding&gt; Element for &lt;configuration&gt;"}]},{"content":"Specifies assembly binding policy at the configuration level.","pos":[686,747]},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>configuration&gt; Element","pos":[754,778]